{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17647227","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17647227"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:42:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:42:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18235"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18235","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18235"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.65,0,0,0.3]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10949"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78446"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10949","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10949"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18235"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63808"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5325"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25447"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25449"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26884"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78446","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78446"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA patient has carpal tunnel syndrome. Numbness and tingling of the fingers is a predominant symptom.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following areas is most likely affected by her symptoms?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Radial three digits","Radial three and a half digits","Radial four digits","Radial four and a half digits","Radial two and a half digits"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms consistent with carpal tunnel syndrome, which is caused by compression of the median nerve as it passes through the carpal tunnel in the wrist. The median nerve provides sensation to the \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial three and a half digits\u003C/strong\u003E, which include the thumb, index finger, middle finger, and the radial half of the ring finger. This distribution of numbness and tingling is characteristic of carpal tunnel syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial four digits\u003C/strong\u003E would include the entire ring finger, which is not typically affected in carpal tunnel syndrome as the ulnar nerve supplies the ulnar half of the ring finger and the little finger.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial four and a half digits\u003C/strong\u003E would include the little finger, which is not affected in carpal tunnel syndrome as it is supplied by the ulnar nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial three digits\u003C/strong\u003E would exclude the radial half of the ring finger, which is typically affected in carpal tunnel syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial two and a half digits\u003C/strong\u003E would exclude the middle finger, which is typically affected in carpal tunnel syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Carpal tunnel syndrome typically presents with numbness and tingling in the radial three and a half digits due to median nerve compression.","The median nerve supplies sensation to the thumb, index finger, middle finger, and the radial half of the ring finger.","Understanding the sensory distribution of the median nerve is crucial for diagnosing carpal tunnel syndrome."],"references":["Genova A, Dix O, Saefan A, Thakur M, Hassan A. Carpal Tunnel Syndrome: A Review of Literature. Cureus. 2020 Mar 19;12(3):e7333. doi: 10.7759/cureus.7333. PMID: 32313774; PMCID: PMC7164699","Dincer, F., \u0026 Samut, G. (2014). Physical examination of the hand. In Hand function: A practical guide to assessment (pp. 23-40). New York, NY: Springer New York","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wojdyla, L., Hughes, T., \u0026 Stelitano, G. (2023). Hand Pathologies. In Textbook of Musculoskeletal Disorders (pp. 675-689). Cham: Springer International Publishing","Mohan, H. (2018). Textbook of pathology. Jaypee Brothers Medical Publishers"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63808"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18235"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63808","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63808"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T20:22:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T20:23:09+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10949"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78446"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identify